<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 94 SUSPECTED GANG MEMBERS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Police Department arrested 94 alleged gang members this weekend 
in its fourth and reportedly "best" anti-gang sweep in the San Fernando Valley, 
a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The law-enforcement effort, known as Operation Hammer and involving about 146 
officers, began Friday night with 131 arrests -- 48 of which involved alleged 
gang members. Another 136 arrests were made between Saturday night and early 
Sunday, including 46 alleged gang members. 
</P>
<P>
"Of the four previous task forces, this was the best," Sgt. John Staugaard said 
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
