<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Linda Ronstadt, Ruben Blades, Jerry Garcia and Santana are set to perform two 
Los Angeles benefit concerts on Aug. 2 in an effort to stem the rising drop-out 
rate among Latino high school students. The shows, with proceeds going to the 
National Hispanic Education and Media Institute, will be held at the Biltmore 
Bowl in the Biltmore Hotel at 7:30 and 10 p.m., followed by a salsa dance 
featuring music by Pancho Sanchez. The concert will be videotaped for airing 
this fall as part of the HBO/Cinemax "Sessions" series. Concert ticket prices 
will range from $50 to $200. Claudia Puig 
</P>
</TEXT>
