<P>
OURAUTOGRAPH PUTS SIGNATURE ON VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ourautograph held off longshot Way Maker by one length and set a stakes record 
of 17.55 seconds while winning the $329,000 Kindergarten Futurity for 
2-year-old quarterhorses Saturday night at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Kip Didericksen, Ourautograph broke evenly from the rail and was 
hustled into the lead, holding off 25-1 shot Way Maker and Teller Cash, who 
went off at 30-1. 
</P>
<P>
Ourautograph, winning for the sixth time in seven career starts, broke the 
record of 17.58 by Tolltac in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
Ourautograph paid $10.60, $6.60 and $5.80. Way Maker paid $18.80 and $4.60, 
with Teller Cash returning $17. 
