<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Perot Ordered to Show Cause: In Fairfax, Va., Circuit Court Judge William 
Plummer ordered H. Ross Perot's new company, Perot Systems Corp., to show cause 
why it should not be held in contempt of court for violating an earlier court 
order. Electronic Data Systems charged that on three occasions PSC violated an 
injunction issued by Plummer prohibiting PSC from "soliciting, negotiating for, 
entering into, or performing any contract or other business relationship" 
before Dec. 1, 1989, that "contemplates or calls for any profitable return at 
any point in time." Plummer issued the order Oct. 21 and made it permanent 
April 13. Under the conditions of his sellout agreement with EDS, Perot agreed 
not to compete with EDS until Dec. 1, 1989. 
