<P>
GANGS CITED IN SANTA ANA KILLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In what Santa Ana police described today as another in a series of gang 
murders, two men approached a parked car and one opened fire with a handgun, 
killing a 16-year-old boy inside the car. 
</P>
<P>
A police spokeswoman said the attack just before midnight Sunday occurred at 
the corner of Spruce and Willits streets, where a man, two women and the 
teen-ager were inside a parked car. 
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman said two men approached the car, an argument broke out and one 
of the men fired at least three times, striking the boy once in the chest. The 
boy died at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
Police withheld the names of the victim, who they said lived in Orange, and 
others in the car. The investigation has been turned over to the gang 
investigations unit, the spokeswoman said. 
</P>
