L.A. MAN NOMINATED JAMAICA ENVOY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
THE HAGUE, Netherlands 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush said today he will nominate Glen A. Holden, a Los Angeles 
insurance executive, to be ambassador to Jamaica. 
</P>
<P>
Holden has been the head of the Holden Group in Los Angeles since 1973. He 
would succeed Michael Sotirhos. 
</P>
<P>
