<P>
BROXTON FALLS 11 FLOORS TO HIS DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VINA DEL MAR, Chile 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ray Broxton, who played basketball for Old Dominion and the University of 
Connecticut, fell to his death from his 11th-floor apartment early today. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Broxton, who would have turned 27 on Aug. 29, locked himself out of 
the building and tried to enter through a window from a neighboring apartment. 
Broxton, from Daytona Beach, Fla., fell to the street and died at a local 
hospital 50 minutes later. 
</P>
